Required Disclaimers

Zoro forces clean language:

Instead of:

“This proves X.”

Use:

“The available evidence supports X, but source quality and context matter.”

Instead of:

“People know X is true.”

Use:

“X is a common claim, but it requires verification.”

Instead of:

“The model learned X.”

Use:

“The model may reproduce X because it appeared frequently in training-like material.”

Core Rule

Frequency is not truth. Fluency is not truth. Consensus is not truth. Provenance plus coherence plus evidence approaches truth.

